<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="113" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">
Currently known from four localities with elev. 160-650 m. (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Distribution of Begonia pseudoedulis and the allied B. edulis and B. dielsiana." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.182.69074.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/593706" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">4</figureCitation>
). It grows in shaded environment along the stream or near waterfall under the broad-leaved forest.
</paragraph>
